CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 29, 1956, pg. 10, reads: "New Club - The Moles, a new socialite group to appear on the local scene, held its Yuletide fete at the home of Ethel Posey Brown in Homestead. Seated are Eloise Brown, Emily Banks, Jean Lewis, President Mary Jones, Ethel Posey Brown and Mabel Starks.  Standing: Ruth Mellix, Frances Douglass, Helen Douglass, Ida Mae Mauney, Isabel Steward and Marguerite Hurd. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of The Moles club, seated from left: Eloise Robinson Brown, Emily Banks, Jean Lewis, Mary Jones, Ethel Posey Brown, Mabel Starks; standing: Ruth Mellix, Frances Douglass, Helen Douglass, Ida Mae Mauney, Isabel Steward, and Marguerite Hurd, posed in Brown home, Homestead, another version
